# Windsurf Rules — LärDigKlockan

## Project
- React Native with Expo (SDK 51+), TypeScript strict mode
- Target platform: iOS (iPhone). Do not add Android-specific workarounds unless asked.
- Use expo-router for all navigation.

## Code style
- TypeScript everywhere — no `any` types
- Functional components with hooks only — no class components
- Name component files with PascalCase, utilities with camelCase
- Keep components small and single-responsibility
- Co-locate types with the file that uses them unless shared across 3+ files

## Styling
- Use React Native StyleSheet.create() for all styles — no inline style objects
- No third-party UI libraries unless explicitly requested
- Design should be child-friendly: large tap targets (min 44pt), readable fonts, soft colors

## State management
- Local state with useState/useReducer unless explicitly told otherwise
- No Redux, Zustand or other state libraries in this project

## Geometry & math
- All clock angle calculations should use radians internally, convert to degrees only for transforms
- Angles: 0 = 12 o'clock position, clockwise positive
- Hour hand formula: (hours % 12 + minutes / 60) * 30 degrees
- Minute hand formula: minutes * 6 degrees

## When implementing gestures
- Use react-native-gesture-handler (comes with Expo)
- Wrap the root in GestureHandlerRootView
- Prefer PanGestureHandler for drag interactions on clock hands

## File structure
src/
  app/          (expo-router screens)
  components/   (reusable UI components)
  constants/    (colors, fonts, layout constants)
  utils/        (pure helper functions)

## Do not
- Do not install packages without explaining why
- Do not use expo-av, expo-camera or other heavy modules unless asked
- Do not auto-format Swedish strings — always use the clockHelpers.ts utility
- Do not use hardcoded colors — always import from constants/colors.ts